<item>
            <title>[SVN-4653] SVN_LOCALE_DIR incorrectly interpolated when prefix is not set explicitly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SVN-4653</link>
                <project id="12318828" key="SVN">Subversion</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When Subversion is compiled from source and &lt;tt&gt;--prefix&lt;/tt&gt; is not passed, &lt;tt&gt;/usr/local&lt;/tt&gt; is assumed but is not correctly passed to &lt;tt&gt;localedir&lt;/tt&gt;, thus &lt;tt&gt;SVN_LOCALE_DIR&lt;/tt&gt; contains a bogus path:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;/tmp/subversion-1.9.4$ sh -x ./configure --libdir=/usr/local/lib/hpux32 --with-apr=/usr/local/apr --with-apr-util=/usr/local/apr  --without-apxs --without-berkeley-db 2&amp;gt; configure.out

/tmp/subversion-1.9.4$ grep LOCALE_DIR subversion/svn_private_config.h
#define SVN_LOCALE_DIR &quot;NONE/share/locale&quot;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you pass &lt;tt&gt;--prefix=/usr/local&lt;/tt&gt; all is fine but is a mere workaround to the issue. I consider lines 210 to 215 in &lt;tt&gt;configure.ac&lt;/tt&gt; to be erronous.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;FreeBSD 9.3, HP-UX 11.31&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="13005700">SVN-4653</key>
